{{Refimprove|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox Organization |name = American Society of Landscape Architects (ASLA) |image = |vision = Leading the design and stewardship of land and communities. |formation = {{start date|1899}} |extinction = |type = Landscape Architecture Society |headquarters = [[Washington, DC]] |location = |membership = 15,428 |language = English |leader_title = President |leader_name = Gregory A. Miller, FASLA<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asla.org/BOT/|title=American Society of Landscape Architects|website=Asla.org|accessdate=30 November 2018}}</ref> |website = http://www.asla.org }}
The '''American Society of Landscape Architects''' ('''ASLA''') is the national professional association representing [[landscape architecture|landscape architects]], with more than 15,000 members in 49 chapters, representing all 50 states, U.S. territories, and 42 countries around the world, plus 72 student chapters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asla.org/aboutasla.aspx|title=About ASLA - asla.org|website=Asla.org|accessdate=30 November 2018}}</ref>
==History== [[File:American Society of Landscape Architects plaque on headquarters building.jpg|thumb|The American Society of Landscape Architects (ASLA) plaque on headquarters building in Washington, DC. Organization founded 1899.]] The group was founded on January 4, 1899, to "establish landscape architecture as a recognized profession in North America", "develop educational studies in landscape architecture", and "provide a voice of authority in the 'New Profession'".{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
A green roof, which covers {{convert|3000|sqft|m2}} on the top of the ASLA headquarters, is to be{{when|date=January 2016}} honoured by Green Roofs for Healthy Cities (GRHC) in the 'Institutional Intensive' category, which honours innovative green roof design in North America, including the countries of the United States, Canada, and Mexico.{{clarify|date=January 2016}}{{citation needed|date=January 2016}}
== Annual Awards == On an annual basis, The American Society of Landscape Architecture gives various awards to professionals and students for design as well as constructed projects in many different categories. These categories range in size, scale and type from small residential areas to large multi acre parks and waterfronts.
==Founding members== * Nathan Barrett * [[Beatrix Jones Farrand]] * [[Daniel W. Langton]] * [[Charles N. Lowrie]] * [[Warren H. Manning]] * [[Frederick Law Olmsted, Jr.]] * [[John Charles Olmsted]] (the Society's first president) * [[Samuel Parsons]], Jr. * [[George F. Pentecost, Jr.]] * [[Ossian Cole Simonds]] * [[Downing Vaux]] (son of [[Calvert Vaux]])
