{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Education of the People's Republic of China |nativename_a = {{nobold|{{lang|zh-hans|中华人民共和国教育部}}}} |nativename_r = {{small|''Zhōnghuá Rénmín Gònghéguó Jiàoyùbù''}} |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal =National Emblem of the People's Republic of China (2).svg |seal_width =150px |seal_caption =[[National Emblem of the People's Republic of China|Emblem of the People's Republic of China]] |formed =September 1954 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = {{PRC}} |headquarters = [[Beijing]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |chief1_name = [[Chen Baosheng]] |chief1_position = Minister of Education |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |parent_agency = [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]] |child1_agency = [[National Office For Teaching Chinese as a Foreign Language]] (NOCFL) |child2_agency = [[China Scholarship Council]] |website = [http://www.moe.edu.cn/publicfiles/business/htmlfiles/moe/moe_2792/index.html www.moe.edu.cn] {{en icon}} |footnotes = }}
The '''Ministry of Education''' ('''MOE''') of the [[Government of China|People's Republic of China]] is the agency of the [[State Council of the People's Republic of China]] that regulates all aspects of the educational system in [[mainland China]], including compulsory basic education, vocational education, and tertiary education. The MOE certifies teachers, standardizes [[curriculum]] and [[textbook]]s, establishes standards, and monitors the entire education system in an effort to "modernize China through education". It is headquartered in [[Xidan]], [[Xicheng District]], Beijing.<ref>[http://www.moe.edu.cn/publicfiles/business/htmlfiles/moe/moe_2792/index.html English home page]. [[Ministry of Education (China)]]. Retrieved on December 29, 2015. "Address: No.37 Damucang Hutong, Xidan, Beijing, P.R.C " - [http://www.moe.edu.cn/publicfiles/business/htmlfiles/moe/s3635/201005/87303.html Chinese address]: "地址：北京市西单大木仓胡同37号 邮编：100816"</ref> The MOE stresses [[technical education]] over other subjects.
The MOE was established in 1949 as the '''Ministry of Education of the Central People's Government,''' and was renamed the '''State Education Commission of the People's Republic of China''' from 1985 to 1998. Its current title was assigned during the restructuring of the State Council in 1998.
